data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression tree construction can be replaced with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no more Expression.Call / Expression.Lambda
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action<...>` signature replaces `Expression<Func<...>>`, so the old code won't compile.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names across complex types are now uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get disambiguated column names (e.g., `Street1`). Pin the old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a => {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a => {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Pin with `HasColumnName()` to keep the old name, or accept the new name and generate a migration.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update all method signatures on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
